obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35851)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35851&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hind Cycles Limited and`
  line `Sen-Raleigh Limited (Nationalisation) Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 15th day of October, 1980.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35852)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35852&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 15th day of October, 1980;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) "Custodian" means the Custodian appointed under sub-section (2) of section 9 to take over, or`
  line `carry on, the management of the undertakings of either, or both, of the two companies;`
  line
  line `(d) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Sen-Raleigh Limited" includes Sen and Pandit Industries Limited, Ancillary Industries (Lugs)`
  line `Private Limited, Ancillary Industries (Forgings) Private Limited, Ancillary Industries (Cranks)`
  line `Private Limited and Naokhali Machine Tools Limited, all having their registered offices at 1,`
  line `Middeton Street, Calcutta;`
  line
  line `(g) "specified date", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of that provision and different dates may`
  line `be specified for different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "two companies" means Hind Cycles Limited and Sen-Raleigh Limited, being companies as`
  line `defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and having their registered offices at Birlagram,`
  line `Nagda (Madhya Pradesh), and 1, Middleton Street, Calcutta, respectively;`
  line
  line `(i) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35853)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the undertakings of the two companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35853&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of each of the two companies, and the right, title`
  line `and interest of each of the two companies in relation to such undertakings, shall, by virtue of the Act,`
  line `stand transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35854)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35854&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of each company referred to in section 3 shall be`
  line `deemed to include all assets, rights, lease-holds, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property,`
  line `movable and immovable, including lands, buildings, workshops, stores, instruments, machinery and`
  line `equipment, cash balances, cash on hand, cheques, demand drafts, reserve funds, investments, book debts,`
  line `and all other rights and interest in, or arising out of, such property as were immediately before the`
  line `appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of such company whether within or outside`
  line `India, and all books of account, registers and all other documents of whatever nature relating thereto, and`
  line `shall also be deemed to include the liabilities specified in sub-section (2) of section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other encumbrances affecting them, and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court`
  line `restricting the use of such properties in any manner or appointing any receiver in respect of the whole or`
  line `any part of such properties shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mortgagee of any property which has vested under this Act in the Central Government and`
  line `every person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such property shall give,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, an intimation to the Commissioner of such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the mortgagee of any property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) or any other person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such`
  line `property shall be entitled to claim, in accordance with his rights and interests, payment of the mortgage`
  line `money or other dues, in whole or in part, out of the amount specified, in relation to the company owning`
  line `such property, in the First Schedule, and also out of the amounts determined under section 8, but no such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest shall be enforceable against any property which has vested in the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any licence or other instrument granted to either of the two companies in relation to any`
  line `undertaking which has vested in the Central Government under section 3 at any time before the appointed`
  line `day and in force immediately before that day shall continue to be in force on and after such day in`
  line `accordance with its tenor in relation to and for the purposes of such undertaking, and, on and from the`
  line `date of vesting of such undertaking under section 6 in a Government company, such Government`
  line `company shall be deemed to be substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other`
  line `instrument had been granted to such Government company and such Government company shall hold it`
  line `for the remainder of the period for which the company to which it was granted would have held it under`
  line `the terms thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature in relation to any`
  line `matter specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, in respect of any undertaking of either of the two`
  line `companies, instituted or preferred by or against either of the two companies, is pending, the same shall`
  line `not abate, be discontinued or be, in any way, prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the`
  line `undertakings of either of two companies or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other`
  line `proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced by or against the Central Government, or, where the`
  line `undertakings of the two companies are directed, under section 6, to vest in Government Companies, by or`
  line `against the concerned Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35855)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Owners of the two Companies to be liable for certain prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35855&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every liability,`
  line `other than the liability specified in sub-section (2), of each of the two companies in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be the liability of the concerned company and shall be enforceable`
  line `against it and not against the Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the two companies are`
  line `directed under section 6, to vest in Government companies, against the concerned Government company.`
  line
  line `(2) Any liability arising in respect of materials supplied to either of the two companies after the`
  line `management of the undertakings of the Company had been taken over by the Central Government shall,`
  line `on and from the appointed day, be the liability of the Central Government or of the concerned`
  line `Government company aforesaid, and shall be discharged by that Government or Government Company,`
  line `as and when repayment for such supplies becomes due and payable.`
  line
  line `(3) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this section or in any other provision of this Act, no`
  line `liability, other than the liability specified in sub-section (2), of either of the two companies in relation`
  line `to its undertakings in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be enforceable against the`
  line `Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the two companies are directed, under section 6,`
  line `to vest in Government companies, against the concerned Government company;`
  line
  line `(b) no award, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of either of the two companies, passed on or after the appointed day, in respect of any`
  line `matter, claim or dispute, not being a matter, claim or dispute in relation to any matter referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), which arose before that day, shall be enforceable against the Central Government, or,`
  line `where the undertakings of the two companies are directed, under section 6, to vest in Government`
  line `companies, against the concerned Government company;`
  line
  line `(c) no liability incurred by either of the two companies before the appointed day, for the`
  line `contravention of any provision of law for the time being in force, shall be enforceable against the`
  line `Central Government, or, where the undertakings of the two companies are directed, under section 6,`
  line `to vest in Government companies, against the concerned Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35883)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakin gs of the two com panies in two Government Companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35883&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, the Central`
  line `Government may, subject to such terms and conditions as it may think fit to impose, direct, by`
  line `notification, that each of the undertakings of the two companies and the right, title and interest of each of`
  line `the two companies in relation to their respective undertakings which have vested in that Government`
  line `under section 3, and such of the liabilities of each of the two companies as are specified in sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 5, shall, instead of continuing to vest in the Central Government, vest in two Government`
  line `companies either on the date of the notification or on such earlier or later date (not being a date earlier`
  line `than the appointed day) as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest, and the liabilities referred to in sub-section (2) of section 5, of`
  line `each of the two companies, in relation to its undertakings, vest in two Government companies under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Government companies shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become owners in relation to such undertakings, and all the rights and liabilities of the Central`
  line `Government in relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become the rights and liabilities, respectively, of the Government companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35857)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35857&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 3, of the undertakings of each of the two companies and the right, title and interest of each of the`
  line `two companies in relation to such undertakings, there shall be given by the Central Government to each of`
  line `the companies, in cash and in the manner specified in Chapter VI, an amount equal to the amount`
  line `specified against the name of such company in the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35858)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of further amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35858&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the deprivation of the two companies of the management`
  line `of their undertakings, there shall be given by the Central Government to each of the companies in cash, an`
  line `amount calculated at the rate specified against the name of such company in the Second Schedule for the period commencing on the date on which the management of the undertakings of such company was`
  line `taken over in pursuance of the orders made by the Central Government under the provisions of the`
  line `Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951(65 of 1951) and ending on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount specified in section 7 and the amount calculated in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall carry simple interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum for the period`
  line `commencing on the appointed day and ending on the date on which payment of such amount is made by`
  line `the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The amounts determined in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be`
  line `given by the Central Government to the two companies in addition to the amount specified in the First`
  line Schedule
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35859)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of the two companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35859&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the undertakings of each of the two`
  line `companies, the right, title and interest in relation to which have vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 3, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6, vest in the Government company specified in such direction; or`
  line
  line `(b) where no such direction has been made by the Central Government, vest in one or more`
  line `Custodians appointed by the Central Government under sub-section (2),`
  line `and thereupon the Government company so specified or the Custodian or Custodians so appointed, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be entitled to exercise, to the exclusion of all other persons, all such powers and do all`
  line `such things as either, or both, of the two companies is or are, authorised to exercise and do in relation to`
  line `its or their undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint one or more individuals or a Government company as the`
  line `Custodian or Custodians of the undertakings of either, or both, of the two companies in relation to which`
  line `no direction has been made by it under sub-section (1) of section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian or Custodians so appointed shall receive, from the funds of the undertakings of the`
  line `two companies, such remuneration as the Central Government may fix and shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35884)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty of persons in charge of management of the undertakings of the two companies to deliver all assets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35884&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the vesting of the management of the undertakings of the two companies`
  line `in Government companies or on the appointment of a Custodian or Custodians, all persons in charge of`
  line `the management of the undertakings of either of the two companies immediately before such vesting or`
  line `appointment, shall be bound to deliver to the concerned Government company or the Custodian or`
  line `Custodians, as the case may be, all assets, books of account, registers or other documents in their custody`
  line `relating to the undertakings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the Government companies or the Custodian or Custodians, and such Government`
  line `companies or the Custodian or Custodians may also, if it is considered necessary so to do, apply to the`
  line `Central Government at any time for instructions as to the manner in which the management of the`
  line `undertakings of the two companies shall be conducted or in relation to any other matter arising in the`
  line `course of such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35861)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty of persons to account for assets, etc., in their possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35861&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who has, on`
  line `the appointed day, in his possession or under his control any assets, books, documents or other papers`
  line `relating to any undertaking owned by the two companies, which have vested in the Central Government`
  line `or in Government companies under this Act, and which belong to the two companies, or would have so`
  line `belonged, if the undertakings owned by the two companies had not vested in the Central Government or`
  line `such Government companies, shall be liable to account for the said assets, books, documents and other papers to the Central Government or the Government companies and shall deliver them up to the Central`
  line `Government or such Government companies or to such person or persons as the Central Government or`
  line `the concerned Government company may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the Government companies aforesaid may take or cause to be taken`
  line `all necessary steps for securing possession of the undertakings of the two companies which have vested in`
  line `the Central Government or the Government companies under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The two companies shall within such period as the Central Government may allow in this behalf,`
  line `furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all their properties and assets, as on the appointed`
  line `day, pertaining to the undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, and, for`
  line `this purpose, the Central Government or the Government companies aforesaid shall afford to the two`
  line `companies all reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35862)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35862&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Custodian or Custodians of the undertakings of either, or both, of the`
  line `two companies shall maintain an account of the undertakings of the concerned company or companies in`
  line `such form and manner and under such conditions as may be prescribed and the provisions of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall apply to the audit of the accounts so maintained as they apply to`
  line `the audit of the accounts of a company.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35885)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Continuance of employees`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35885&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who has been, immediately before the appointed`
  line `day, employed in any undertaking of either of the two companies shall become,--`
  line
  line `(a) on and from the appointed day, an employee of the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the undertakings of the two companies are directed, under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6, to vest in Government Companies, an employee of the concerned Government company on`
  line `and from the date of such vesting or transfer;`
  line `and shall hold office or service under the Central Government or the concerned Government company, as`
  line `the case may be, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters as would`
  line `have been admissible to him if there had been no such vesting and shall continue to do so unless and until`
  line `his employment under the Central Government or the concerned Government company, as the case may`
  line `be, is duly terminated or until his remuneration and other conditions of service are duly altered by the`
  line `Central Government or the Concerned Government company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other person employed`
  line `in any undertaking of either of the two companies, to the Central Government or a Government company,`
  line `shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation under this Act or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35886)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provident fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35886&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where either of the two companies has established a`
  line `provident fund, superannuation, welfare or other fund for the benefit of the persons employed in any of its`
  line `undertakings, the moneys relatable to the officers or other employees whose services have become`
  line `transferred by or under this Act to the Central Government or Government company shall, out of the`
  line `moneys standing, on the appointed day, to the credit of such provident fund, superannuation, welfare or`
  line `other fund, stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central Government or the concerned Government`
  line `company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The moneys which stand transferred under sub-section (1) to the Central Government or the`
  line `Government company, as the case may be, shall be dealt with by that Government or Government`
  line `company in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35864)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35864&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the`
  line `purpose of disbursing the amounts payable under sections 7 and 8 to each of the two companies, by`
  line `notification, appoint a Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35865)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Payment by Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35865&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall,`
  line `within thirty days from the specified date, pay in cash to the Commissioner, for payment to each of the`
  line `two companies,--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the amount specified against the name of such company in the First`
  line `Schedule; and`
  line
  line `(b) an amount equal to the amount payable to each of the two companies under section 8.`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government in favour of the Commissioner in`
  line `the Public Account of India and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be deposited`
  line `by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated by the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `(3) Separate records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of the undertakings of each`
  line `of the two companies in relation to which payments have been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Interest accruing on the amount standing to the credit of the deposit account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall enure to the benefit of the two companies.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35866)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Certain powers of Central Government or Government companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35866&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government or the concerned Government company, as the case may be, shall be entitled to receive up to`
  line `the specified date, to the exclusion of all other persons, any money due to either of the two companies in`
  line `relation to the undertakings which have vested in the Central Government or the Government company`
  line `and realised after the appointed day, notwithstanding that the realisation pertains to a period prior to the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, or the concerned Government company, as the case may be, may make`
  line `a claim to the Commissioner with regard to every payment made by that Government or Government`
  line `company after the appointed day, for discharging any liability of either of the two companies, not being`
  line `any liability specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, in relation to any period prior to the appointed day,`
  line `and every such claim shall have priority, in accordance with the priorities attaching, under this Act, to the`
  line `matter in relation to which such liability has been discharged by the Central Government or the`
  line `Government company.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the liabilities or either of the two companies in respect of`
  line `any transaction prior to the appointed day which have not been discharged on or before the specified date`
  line `shall be the liabilities of the respective company.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35867)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35867&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every person having a claim against either of the`
  line `two companies with regard to any of the matters specified in the Third Schedule pertaining to any`
  line `undertaking owned by it shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within thirty days from the`
  line `specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, he may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days, but not thereafter`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35868)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Priority of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35868&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The claims made under section 18 shall have priorities in accordance with`
  line `the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Category I shall have precedence over all other categories and Category II shall have`
  line `precedence over Category III, and so on;`
  line
  line `(b) the claims specified in each of the categories shall rank equally and be paid in full, but, if the`
  line `amount is insufficient to meet such claims in full, they shall abate in equal proportions and be paid`
  line `accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the question of discharging any liability with regard to a matter specified in a lower category`
  line `shall arise only if a surplus is left after meeting all the liabilities specified in the immediately higher`
  line category.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35869)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Examination of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35869&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the claims made under section 18, the Commissioner`
  line `shall arrange the claims in the order of priorities specified in the Third Schedule and examine the same in`
  line `accordance with such order.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on examination of the claims, the Commissioner is of opinion that the amount paid to him`
  line `under this Act is not sufficient to meet the liabilities specified in any lower category, he shall not be`
  line `required to examine the claims in respect of such lower category.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35870)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Admission or rejection of the claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35870&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `.(1) After examining the claims with reference to the`
  line `priorities specified in the Third Schedule, the Commissioner shall fix a date on or before which every`
  line `claimant shall file the proof of his claim.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fourteen days notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of any daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country`
  line `and in one issue of any daily newspaper in such regional language as the Commissioner may consider`
  line `suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant to file the proof of his claim with the`
  line `Commissioner within the period specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claimant who fails to file the proof of his claim within the period specified by the`
  line `Commissioner shall be excluded from the disbursements made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and after`
  line `giving the concerned company an opportunity of refuting the claim and after giving the claimant a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, admit or reject the claim in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out of`
  line `the discharge of his functions including the place or places at which he may hold his sitting and shall, for`
  line `the purpose of making any investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a Civil`
  line `Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(6) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Civil Court for the purposes of section 195, and Chapter XXVI, of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974 ).`
  line
  line `(7) A claimant who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner, may prefer an appeal`
  line `against such decision to the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the registered office of the concerned company is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who is a Judge of a High Court is appointed to be the Commissioner,`
  line `such appeal, shall lie to the High Court exercising jurisdiction over the place in which the registered`
  line `office of the concerned company is situated and such appeal shall be heard and disposed of by not less`
  line `than two Judges of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35871)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disbursement of money by the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35871&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `—After admitting a claim under this Act, the`
  line `amount due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to the person or persons to whom`
  line `such amount is due, and on such payment, the liability of each of the two companies in respect of such`
  line `claim shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35872)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disbursement of amounts to the two companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35872&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, out of the moneys paid to him in`
  line `relation to the undertakings of either of the two companies, there is a balance left after meeting the`
  line `liabilities as specified in the Third Schedule, the Commissioner shall disburse such balance to the`
  line `concerned company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any machinery, equipment or other property has vested in the Central`
  line `Government or a Government company under this Act, but such machinery, equipment or other property`
  line `does not belong to either of the two companies, it shall be lawful for the Central Government or the`
  line `concerned Government company, to continue to possess such machinery or equipment or other property`
  line `on the same terms and conditions under which they were possessed by either of the companies`
  line `immediately before the appointed day`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35873)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amount to be deposited with the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35873&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the office of the Commissioner is finally wound up, shall be transferred by`
  line `the Commissioner, before his office is finally would up, to the general revenue account of the Central`
  line `Government; but a claim to any money so transferred may be preferred to the Central Government by the`
  line `person entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been made, and the`
  line `order, if any, for the payment of the claim being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35874)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35874&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument having`
  line `effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or other`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35887)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by the Central Government or Government companies .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35887&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into by either of the two companies in relation to any of its`
  line `undertakings which has vested in the Central Government under section 3 for any service, sale or supply,`
  line `and in force immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from the expiry of a period of thirty days`
  line `from the appointed day, cease to have effect unless such contract is, before the expiry of that period,`
  line `ratified, in writing, by the Central Government or the Government company concerned, in which such`
  line `undertaking has been vested under this Act and in ratifying such contract, the Central Government or such`
  line `Government company may make such alteration or modification therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or the such Government company shall not omit to ratify a`
  line `contract and shall not make any alteration or modification in a contract--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous or has been entered into in bad faith`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or such Government company; and`
  line
  line `(b) except after giving the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35876)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35876&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `either of the two companies, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or the`
  line `Government company concerned; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of or retains, any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `either of the two companies; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the Government company`
  line `concerned or any person or body of persons specified by that Government or such Government`
  line `company, any document relating to such undertaking, which may be in his possession, custody or`
  line `control; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government or the Government company concerned or any`
  line `person or body of persons specified by that Government or Government company, any assets, books`
  line `of account, registers or other documents in his possession, custody or control, relating to the`
  line `undertakings of either of the two companies; or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of any undertaking of either of the`
  line `two companies or prefers any claim which he knows or has reason to believe to be false or grossly`
  line inaccurate,
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35877)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35877&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35878)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35878&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the Custodian or the`
  line `Government companies or other person authorised by that Government or Government companies for`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any of its officers or`
  line `other employees or the Custodian or the Government companies or any officer or other person authorised`
  line `by those companies for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35879)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35879&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by this section and sections 31 and 32 may also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35880)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35880&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely,--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, an intimation referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4 shall be given;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which, and the conditions under which, the Custodian or Custodians`
  line `shall maintain the accounts as required by section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the moneys in any provident fund or other fund, referred to in section 14,`
  line `shall be dealt with;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (35881)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35881&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (35882)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388&sectionId=35882&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_51_00002_198070_1517807325388
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Hind Cycles Limited and Sen-Raleigh Limited (Nationalisation)`
  line `Ordinance, 1980 (16 of 1980), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance so repealed`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
